Author: SemicolonButterfly
Text: Over such an extended time period period, the difference (calorie math wise) between 0.3kg and 2kg seems like it’s within the uncertainty limits for TDEE estimates.   I really struggle to accurately perceive my weight changes. I’ll feel certain I’m getting bigger or smaller but then pictures, measurements, or the scale say otherwise. It’s very disorienting, and like you said it makes it challenging to know what’s real and what to trust.

Author: novadelfuego
Text: Maybe when you initially weighed yourself you had a lot of water weight so you actually initially weighed less that you thought?
